You said:
one user can raise many complaints one to many relation between user and complaint
ChatGPT said:
You're absolutely right â€” if one user can raise many complaints, then the relationship between User and Complaint should be:

One-to-Many from User â†’ Complaint
Many-to-One from Complaint â†’ User

Let me show you exactly how to model that in your JPA entities:

âœ… 1. User Entity (One-to-Many side)
Add this to your User entity:

@OneToMany(mappedBy = "user", cascade = CascadeType.ALL, orphanRemoval = true)
private List<Complaint> complaints = new ArrayList<>();
Example (Partial User entity):
@Entity
@Data
public class User {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;

    private String name;
    private String email;
    private String password;
    private String role;

    // One user â†’ many complaints
    @OneToMany(mappedBy = "user", cascade = CascadeType.ALL, orphanRemoval = true)
    private List<Complaint> complaints = new ArrayList<>();
}
âœ… 2. Complaint Entity (Many-to-One side)
Already mostly done, just ensure it's written like this:

@ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
@JoinColumn(name = "user_id", nullable = false)
private User user;
Example (Partial Complaint entity):
@Entity
@Data
public class Complaint {

    @Id
    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)
    private Long id;

    private String title;
    private String description;
    private String status = "OPEN";

    private LocalDateTime createdAt = LocalDateTime.now();

    // Many complaints â†’ one user
    @ManyToOne(fetch = FetchType.LAZY)
    @JoinColumn(name = "user_id", nullable = false)
    private User user;
}
ğŸ§  Why use mappedBy, cascade, and orphanRemoval?
mappedBy = "user": Tells JPA the owning side is in the Complaint entity.

cascade = CascadeType.ALL: Automatically cascades operations (e.g., save user â†’ saves complaints).

orphanRemoval = true: Removes complaint if itâ€™s removed from the userâ€™s list.

âœ… Now What?
With this setup, you can:

Call user.getComplaints() to get all complaints by that user.

Save a complaint with complaint.setUser(user) and it will link properly.

Let me know if you want to add bidirectional JSON serialization (for APIs) with @JsonManagedReference / @JsonBackReference to avoid infinite recursion!

